Parliament, Friday 11 September 2020 – National Assembly Deputy Speaker Mr. Lechesa Tsenoli will today address a webinar on Civil Society Participation in the legislative sector programme.
	
	The webinar, hosted by the Northern Cape Provincial Legislature, will explore ways of strengthening inclusive public participation during COVID-19 and beyond, using virtual platforms.
	
	Deputy Speaker will speak on the “Impact of the 4th Industrial Revolution on Parliaments.”
	
	Details of the webinar are as follows:
	
	Date: Friday, 11 September 2020
	Time: 12 noon
	Venue: Virtual platform
	
	The webinar is open to the media and the public. Journalists wishing to cover it should send their cellphone numbers to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communication Services WhatsApp Group, where a link to the session will be shared. Journalists must send these requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
